<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Character Moves Between Servers Possible?</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=451607" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <p>
I received this note from <a href="mailto:bio-hazard@home.com">Torlin Outsider</a> regarding an inquiry made to the Head GM of E'ci. Apparently Verant is planning on making it possible to move characters from one server or another. This is completely unconfirmed so dont jump out of your seat just yet!</p>
<p>
During the Everquest Fan Faire II, this issue was brought up and was said to be a considered option with certain losses in the process, IE: naked transfer (no money or equipment). Here is the message from Torlin:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>
This is a email I recieved from the Head GM on E'ci when I emailed him and inquired about moving characters from server to server. I would suggest people to email there head GM's or the tech help and request this, to let them know there are quite a few people who would like to move servers.</p>
<blockquote>
<i><p>
Greetings,</p>
<p>
We are in the process of setting up a system that allows you to move characters for a fee.  However, I am afraid that I do not have any details about it yet.</p>
<p>
Keep watching patch messages for any news.</p>
<p>
GM Therdar - E'ci<br>
Rick Alvernaz<br>
Sony Online Entertainment<br>
xxxxxxxxx@station.sony.com<br>
http://www.station.sony.com</p></i>
</blockquote>
<p>
Tis Great News Indeed,<br>
Torlin Outsider Rogue Of Zub Zub</p>
</blockquote>
We'll dig deeper into the issue and hopefully we can confirm this! I had removed the GM's email address to prevent him from being bombarded with email.
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
		     <br><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a href="UserUpdate.asp?id=451607">[Add Comments] Please Add your comments here!</a></b></font><br><hr>
			  </td>
		</tr>

		</table>

	</td>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
