			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I don't think allowing players to make a one-time transfer of their characters, platinum and equipment to a different server would greatly affect a server's economy.  I would think that people would probably move to servers their RL friends play on and that the jostling would be somewhat proportional.  I mean, for the most part, it should balance out on the blue servers.  The economies on RP and PvP servers may go a bit off kilter, but that would actually be because more people would actually be utilizing those particular servers.  I currently play on Tallon, but I would love to have the one-time opportunity to move my characters to hook up with some RL friends.<BR>
<BR>
My 2cp
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
