	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Let's see... just no drop transfer.. Well lets see... Full suit of Totemic along with +4 wis jewelry,Imbued armor, and a half way decent 1hb weapon.... *poof*... Full suit of crafted with YAK, Cane of Tranq, Sebelite scale mantle, +4str +2 intel earrings, and a couple plat fire wedding bands, Various other weapons for raising combat skills.... *poof*.... Ravenscale, orc fang earrings and necklace, plat BP rings, Dwarven workboots, Various weapons for raising skills, and a few for actual hunting.... *poof*... Full suit of shadowbound, +4 intel +2 str earrings, +4 intel rings, dagger of marnak, staff of writhing, harvester..... *poof*... See a pattern yet??? No drop items are not widely used and are NOT really needed unless it happens to be armor or weaponry which Not too many people have enough of that type of gear or are even high enough level to obtain the gear to allow just No Drop items. There are too many people that have spent hundreds of hours getting their gear to give it up, and very very few that would want to go through 8 and 9 hour spawns again just to get what they had. And even then they'd be lucky to get it then because most of the time the spawn doesn't drop what is needed. Or in shadowbound armor's case... getting the schedule worked out again to do a painstakingly long quest with a lot of No rent items that you lose if you happen to sneeze wrong and go Link Dead. I've only got one character With any decent gear really, and He's only 38. Can't get planar armor yet... can't get any of the velious quest only no drop armor yet... All I can and have gotten is Crafted... and For only having a few hours to play here and there, it was a struggle that I'd rather not repeat. Think about those with the limited time frames to play. For someone that get maybe 4 or 5 hours a week to play, the re-equipping would be so much of a pain, it'd almost be easier on them to just start over from level 1. And besides.. What's the difference between ! set of armor on this server.... guy knows he can't take it so he gives it away to a newb.... then goes and gets the same armor on new server... There is the extra set on the new server anyway, because with broke transfers as well, it's not like they can buy armor that is currently on the system. The extra armor will be there no matter what and the economy will still reflect that. But instead of one suit on one server.. there is one on each, quested and created by that same player. At least the gear being worn is Used gear... it's not like they'd sell it all and start naked. The transfer would make more sense to transfer worn gear and held money. Nothing in the bank, just what is on the characters body and in his wallet, that way excess gear can be sold on old server, and replacement bought on new server if possible. By excess I mean the optional gear most have to keep skills trained... or to use as a change of pace. At least the on character's body transfer would limit the stuff moved to the stuff that the character actually uses. That way they can't bank a stockpile to bring with them and sell or give away. And there is no reason not to allow money transfers as it allows the character to buy existing stuff on the new server... which would allow prices on it to stay constant and allow people to still make their money to buy bigger and better things. Naked transfers would only worsen the presence of the &quot;e-bay&quot; character that has the best of everything for each character on the account, and can't play the characters for crap and winds up getting the whole group killed about a dozen times before finally logging off or leaving the group. Not saying all are that bad, was just using an example from personal experience. Now that I've rambled for long enough... Have a nice day
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
