				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Agreed. I'd even be willing to start my characters at level 1 rather than lose the gear.... Gear transfer from server to server is a lot easier than level transfer because the people transfering them have to actully play the characters to get the levels and skills up to what they were on the previous server. That is why server splits are not that Common. There are several crowded servers due to this... And this was told to me by more that one person whose been involved in such transfers. They can't use a hex to get the skills and levels up. They could have been juerkin my chain, but then again.. they could be right. With a gear and Character transfer with a level cut, that'd greatly simplify the task... Or even make a minimum level requirement to transfer characters. Put it at say 20 or 25 after the characters are actually able to do the quests for the better gear and not tempted to restart the character so readily. Just My 2 coppers worth. But anything is better than a naked Transfer. I'd hate to run around with a Naked Level 41 warrior wielding a rusty sword and Tattered armor on my back. Or a caster with only his base intel to depend on for mana.. &lt;shudder&gt;. Or any class at base and naked for that matter. It would take way too long to get back to the same gear you had. Money isn't as important as gear... gear is survival and ability to hunt and raid with those of your level. Who ever heard of a Level 50 wearing all leather and a newbie weapon going on a plains raid? 
